n: Code space Notation <p>We have that</p> \[  egin{align*}     \F^n(A) &amp;=  igcup_{i=1}^N f_i(A) \     &amp;=  igcup_{i_1, ..., i_n=1}^N f_{i_1} \circ ... \circ f_{i_n}(A) 	ab (*) \end{align*} \] <p>Using elements from the code space \(\S_N\), we denote</p> \[ egin{align*}     \s(n)&amp;:=(\s_1, ..., \s_n) \     f_{\s(n)}&amp;:=f_{\s_1} \circ ... \circ f_{\s_n} \end{align*}\] <p>Using this notation, we can reformulate \((*)\) to  </p> \[  egin{align*}     \F^n(A) &amp;=  igcup_{\s(n) \in \S_N} f_{\s(n)}(A) \     \A &amp;= \lim_{n	o\infty}  igcup_{\s(n) \in \S_N} f_{\s(n)}(A) \end{align*} \] Proposition: Completeness of the code space Theorem 4 <p>Define</p> \[  egin{align*}     \gamma : \S_N &amp; 	o \alpha \     \s &amp; \mapsto \lim_{n	o\infty} f_{\s(n)} (x) \end{align*} \] \[\gamma 	ext{ is continuous, and independent of } x\in X\] Proof Existence and uniquenessContinuitySurjectivity <p>\( egin{align*}     	ext{Let } &amp;x, y\in X \     &amp;L:=\max_{1\le i\le N} \Lip f_i \end{align*}\)</p> <p>Assuming without loss of generality that \(X\) is compact:</p> \[  egin{align*}     \implies |f_{\s(n)}(x)-f_{\s(n)}(y)|     &amp; \le L^n |x-y| \     &amp; \le L^n \diam X \     |f_{\s(m)}(x)-f_{\s(n)}(y)| &amp; \le L^{n'} \diam X &amp; n':=\min\{n, m\} \end{align*} \] <p>We get a cauchy sequence in \(\S_N\) independent of \(x\in X\). Thus, the limit exists and is unique. \(	ab\square\)</p> <p>Let \(\varepsilon &gt;0\)</p> \[  egin{align*}     \implies      egin{cases}         \exists\ n \in \N 	ext{ s.t.} \         L^n \diam X &lt; \varepsilon     \end{cases} \end{align*} \] <p>\( egin{align*}     	ext{Let } &amp; \s, 	au \in \S_N 	ext{ s.t.} \     &amp; \s(n) = 	au(n) \end{align*}\)</p> <p>Then, we get</p> \[  egin{align*}     d_F(\s, 	au)     &amp;= \sum_{i=n+1}^\infty  rac{\varepsilon}{1-L} &lt;  rac{1}{(N+1)^n} \     \implies |\gamma(\s)-\gamma(	au)|     &amp;= \lim_{n	o\infty} |f_{\s(n)}(x)-f_{tau(n)}(y)| \     &amp; \le L^n \diam X &lt; \varepsilon &amp; \squar